records.addlTxt:
09:44 AM Defendant William J Feavel in court, in custody, with attorney Angela Wang.   Patrick Ryan Campbell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

The Court conducts a plea colloquy with the Defendant.
The Defendant pleads no contest to Count 1.
The Court finds the Defendant guilty of Count 1.
Count 2 is dismissed and read into Count 1 & 21CF1267

The State gives its sentencing recommendation.
The Defense gives its sentencing recommendations.
The Defendant presents a statement.



The Defendant was sentenced to the following:



IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   


7 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 43 days)
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  5 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

IF REVOKED: 
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program only after 18 months of incarceration. 
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

TERM OF PROBATION:  5 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No use or possession of CBD or vaping products;
*Full physiological evalution and comply with any treatment;
*No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores);
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel in Waukesha County within 6 months of release from custody, and is to attend EVERY Victim Impact Panel while on extended supervision;
*Do not drive or operate a motor vehicle without a valid license; Comply with all drivers licensing restrictions; 
* 2 self help meetings per week and to attend in person;
*DNA sample to be provided;


COURT COSTS:  WAIVED
DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00
   - to be paid as a condition of probation.

*Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
*Body Armour warnings given.
